

What does server know?
Server has a gameState.
Server has a actionQueue for handling actions retrived from packets. 
At the end of each turn, Server calls actionQueue.forEach().eval.
Each action have the property to determine if it change the global state of the gameState;.

When an action.eval() changes the gameState, it return a result which is an object that whole changed properties in gameState;
In gameState class:

``

function update(actionQueue) {
    const result = actionQueue.map(action => action.eval());
    applyChanges(result);
}
``



Server: instance of the server.
s_handler: handle arrived packets, server side.

Client: instance of the client
c_handler: handle arrived packets, client side.

GameState: the current state of the game
ActionQueue: action that need to update on game state



